Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Abstract", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.36543301197627*^9, 3.365433014101*^9}}],

Cell["\<\
We will discuss knapsack problems that arise in certain computational number \
theory settings. A common theme is that the search space for the standard \
real relaxation is large; in a sense this translates to a poor choice of \
variables. Lattice reduction methods have been developed in the past few \
years to improve handling of such problems. We show explicitly how they may \
be applied to computation of Frobenius instances,  Keith numbers (also called \
\"repfigits\"), and as a first step in computation of Frobenius numbers.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.36543302298607*^9, 3.36543302680631*^9}}]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

