Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Other problems under consideration in this talk", "Subsubsection"],

Cell["Find Keith numbers (first we must define them...)", "Outline2"],

Cell["\<\
Solve the \"Frobenius instance\" problem (aka \"postage stamp\" or \"change\
\[Hyphen]making\" problem).\
\>", "Outline2"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Compute the Frobenius number for a given set of nonnegative integers whose \
GCD is unity.\
\>", "Outline2"],

Cell["\<\
The common feature to these problems will be that we take restricted integer \
combinations of integer vectors to fulfill some task. That is to say, we work \
with sets of constrained linear diophantine equations. This is really just a \
mild generalization of the classical subset sum problem.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.3654349802199*^9, 3.36543502575911*^9}}]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

