Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Frobenius instances and Frobenius numbers", "Section"],

Cell["We mention in brief Frobenius instances and numbers.", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.36544206904395*^9, 3.36544207965144*^9}}],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Statement of the Frobenius instance problem", "Subsubsection"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Given a set of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["n", TraditionalForm]]],
 " positive integers in increasing order ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"A", "=", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      FormBox[
       SubscriptBox["a", "1"],
       TraditionalForm], ",", "...", ",", 
      FormBox[
       SubscriptBox["a", "n"],
       TraditionalForm]}], "}"}]}], TraditionalForm]]],
 ", we wish to know when a given positive integer ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["k", TraditionalForm]]],
 " can be written as a nonnegative integer combination of the elements of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["A", TraditionalForm]]],
 " (if we relax the nonnegativity constraint on the multipliers, then clearly \
it can be done iff ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["k", TraditionalForm]]],
 " is a multiple of the GCD of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["A", TraditionalForm]]],
 ")."
}], "Text"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This problem goes by other names, among them the postage stamp problem \
(given several stamp denominations, how to obtain a given total value?), the \
chicken McNugget problem (how to get ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["k", TraditionalForm]]],
 " McNuggets from orders of size 6, 9, or 20?), and the change making problem \
(for equally obvious reasons)."
}], "Text"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

