Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Big Keith numbers", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.36544194185921*^9}],

Cell[TextData[{
 "One will observe that all of these begin with digits in {1,2,9} and end \
with digits in {0,2,4,5,6,7}. If these were in some way \"random\" and \
uniform we would believe the probability of this limited set of first digits \
occuring exclusively to be ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    FractionBox["1", "3"], ")"}], "13"]]],
 ", or about ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FractionBox["1", 
   SuperscriptBox["10", "6"]]]],
 ". The probability of the last digits being so restricted is a tame one\
\[Hyphen]in\[Hyphen]a\[Hyphen]thousand or so. This raises an obvious \
conjecture and a perhaps unusual question: Might there be something \
intrinsically \"interesting\" to Keith numbers that would keep them from \
being \"random\"?"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.36544153466495*^9, 3.36544157208644*^9}, {
  3.36544190980559*^9, 3.36544191847857*^9}}],

Cell["\<\
So I checked further. After a few computer\[Hyphen]days I found the only two \
29 digit Keith numbers.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.3654418224169*^9, 3.36544182637678*^9}}],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
  "4", ",", "1", ",", "7", ",", "9", ",", "6", ",", "2", ",", "0", ",", "5", 
   ",", "7", ",", "6", ",", "5", ",", "1", ",", "4", ",", "7", ",", "4", ",", 
   "2", ",", "6", ",", "9", ",", "7", ",", "4", ",", "7", ",", "0", ",", "4", 
   ",", "7", ",", "9", ",", "1", ",", "5", ",", "2", ",", "8"}], 
  "}"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{"{", 
  RowBox[{
  "7", ",", "0", ",", "2", ",", "6", ",", "7", ",", "3", ",", "7", ",", "5", 
   ",", "5", ",", "1", ",", "0", ",", "2", ",", "0", ",", "7", ",", "8", ",", 
   "8", ",", "5", ",", "2", ",", "4", ",", "2", ",", "2", ",", "1", ",", "8", 
   ",", "8", ",", "3", ",", "7", ",", "4", ",", "0", ",", "4"}], 
  "}"}]}], "DisplayFormula"],

Cell["\<\
Both violate the seemingly strong trend of first digits, and one violates the \
last digit trend as well. So this becomes a much weaker conjecture that there \
might be a mathematical justification for \"most\" large Keith numbers to fit \
the trend patterns.\
\>", "Text"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

